Class BaseLocationUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.dom.BaseLocationUtils

    • Method Detail

      • getParameter

        static String getParameter​(BaseLocation location,
                           String name)
        Gets the URL parameter of the specified name.
        Note that if multiple parameters have been specified with the same name, the last one will be returned.
        Parameters:
        location - location DOM item with URL page definition
        name - the name of the URL parameter
        Returns:
        the value of the URL parameter, or null if missing

      • getParameterMap

        static Map<String,​List<String>> getParameterMap​(BaseLocation location)
        Returns an unmodifiable map of the URL query parameters for the host page at the time this method was called.
        Any changes to the window's location will be reflected in the result of subsequent calls.
        Parameters:
        location - location DOM item with URL page definition
        Returns:
        a map from URL query parameter names to a list of values

      • checkAndLoadParametersMap

        private static void checkAndLoadParametersMap​(BaseLocation location)
        Checks the consistency of parameters map and loads it if not yet done or if URL query string is change.
        Parameters:
        location - location DOM item with URL page definition

      • loadParametersMap

        private static void loadParametersMap​(String queryString)
        Builds an unmodifiable map that contains all parameters, parsed from query string.
        Parameters:
        queryString - the query string of URL of document
